  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> And it would make sense to clean up because there is no mean to opt out part of the store. Also, applying some ui filters that were hidden by a user action is not a straightforward behavior. I mean you hide something and yet it stills applies is confusing, right?\n\nYes I would say this should be the default behavior. But at the same time I would understand people doing things like show/hide only for UI simplification purposes, like implementing collapsible facets/accordion that would ultimately not render the RefinementList while the refinements would still be applied.\n\nMaybe for now what we could do is only document and precise the current behavior in the guide? Then given user feedbacks we will decide what is the best behavior to implement?\n",
